Candidate for IEBC chairperson David Mukii Mereka, 64, has withdrawn from the race.He told the selection panel that he took the decision to give chance for younger applicants. Mereka, a veteran lawyer said he would be glad if the position is taken by a female nominee."I hope in respect to the gender rule the select panel will nominate a lady to fill in the slot i have left open," he said."I have decided to step aside so i can give room for younger generations to take charge of the IEBC commission," he said.Mereka, from Muranga was among the five candidates eyeing the position of chairperson of the IEBC.Read: Selection panel shortllists five candidates for IEBC chair